ical, and religious control.     Tracing these developments through many of the past century’s major conflagrations, Dimsdale narrates how when World War II erupted, governments secretly raced to develop drugs for interrogation. Brainwashing returned to the spotlight during the Cold War in the hands of the North Koreans and Chinese. In response, a huge Manhattan Project of the Mind was established to study memory obliteration, indoctrination during sleep, and hallucinogens. Cults used the techniques as well. Nobel laureates, university academics, intelligence operatives, criminals, and clerics all populate this shattering and dark story—one that hasn’t yet ended.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBrainwashingxHistory. 0aControl (Psychology). 0aSocial control. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Englishz978311075414808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021z9783110753912oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030026246940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262469423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300262469/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075414-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DPMb2021